HEADWORD: chauguette
<hw>⟦Eacute⟧`chau`guette"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A small chamber or place of protection for a
sentinel, usually in the form of a projecting turret, or the like. See
<er>Castle</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eche</ent>⟦br⟧
